// @check
// @error argument of type string flows into `g` expecting i32
// SOUNDNESS. An un-annotated param is an inference HOLE; a hole flowing as an
// argument into a CONCRETE parameter can't be judged inside the generic body
// (a hole is permissively assignable both ways). The demand is recorded and
// re-validated at the generic call site under the substituted argument types
// (the deferred binary-op-constraint pattern). Before this check `f("hello")`
// compiled clean and produced invalid wasm at run.
function g(n: i32) { return n + 1 }
function f(x) { return g(x) }
print(f("hello")) // REJECTED: string flows into g's i32 param
